"""In this exercise, you will create a program that begins by reading a measurement
in feet from the user. Then your program should display the equivalent distance in
inches, yards and miles. Use the Internet to look up the necessary conversion factors
if you donâ€™t have them memorized."""

#1 foot are 12 inches
#1 foot are 1/3 yards
#1 foot are 0.000189394 miles

feet = int(input("Please, introduce a distance measured in feet: "))
inches = feet*12
yards = round(feet*1/3,3)
miles = round(feet*0.000189394,3)

print("The distance {} expressed in feet is \n\t{} inches\n\t{} yards and\n\t{} miles".format(feet,inches, yards, miles))
